Cape Town - A man died on Sunday evening after he lost control of his car in Vanderbijlpark and was ejected, Gauteng paramedics said. “Bystanders on the scene pointed paramedics in the direction of where they found a man lying in the nearby veld,’ ER24 said in a statement. The man, in his early thirties, appeared to have been the only occupant of the car. His vehicle overturned several times before coming to a standstill in the open veld. ER24 said paramedics could not do anything for the man and he was declared dead on the scene.